msgstr ""

#: ../../source/data_integrity.rst:88 ee9b42d848844d23a2e6b72edfa896c6
msgid ""
"Is there anything related to the 1 Battalion’s parent or child units that "
"may impact where it was based?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/data_integrity.rst:89 e118fc1c6ffa4c719def07818e7f7aaa
msgid ""
"Are there any other mitigating sources (i.e. major restructuring of the "
"military, constitutional changes, etc.) which may impact the basing of the "
"unit?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/data_integrity.rst:90 524da0a191864cc1952256509e010c34
msgid "Is more research needed before the Monitor can make any claim?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/data_integrity.rst:92 cb9ce86089f14002b01d86b1ac14fc30
msgid ""
"An argument could be the Monitor should always make “separate claims” as "
"that would be more faithful to the sources. However, the result likely mean "
"an almost incomprehensible amount of detail in the records of people and "
"units, which would obscure when changes really did occur, for instance when "
"a person changed positions or a unit ends operations in an area."
